U_{1}\sim U(0,1)
U_{1}-U_{1}
A,B
A=B=U_{1}
U_{1}-U_{1}
P(A-B\leq x)=\int_{0}^{1}P(A\leq u,B \geq u-x)du
P(U_{1}-U_{1}\leq x)=\int_{0}^{1}P(U_{1}\leq u,U_{1} \geq u-x)du
=\int_{0}^{1}P(u-x\leq U_{1}\leq u)du=\int_{0}^{1}xdu=x
-1 \lt x \lt 0
0 \lt x \lt 1
P(A-B \lt x)= \int_{a=0}^{1+x} \int_{b=a-x}^{1} \,db \,da=\int_{a=0}^{1+x} (1-a+x) \,da =\frac{(1+x)^2}{2}
P(A-B \lt x)=1-\frac{(1-x)^2}{2}.
